<p>On Linux, you can easily tell the linker to emit a warning when the function is linked, e.g. like this:</p>  <pre><code>static const char blah_msg[] __attribute__((section(".gnu.warning.blah"))) =     "blah() is deprecated. Use blub()."; </code></pre>  <p>How to implement this warning behaviour on Solaris 10?</p>  <p>(i.e. with Solaris Studio and the Solaris <code>ld</code>)</p>